ce:section.ce:para:
The WS-10 and WS-10 – Cd2+ ions fluorescence decay was measured and interpreted in Fig. 6
                        . The lifetimes of synthesised WS-10 carbon nanomaterial were found to be very short, as shown by the black line in the figure, implying a fast-exciting recombination process with an average lifetime of 3.46 ns. Furthermore, the decay processes investigated with Cd2+ ions (red line), revealed a significant increase in the decay component, which holds with an average lifetime of 5.14 ns (Table 1
                        ). These findings demonstrated that the addition of Cd2+ ions reduced the fluorescence intensity, confirming the successful detection of analyte using synthesised WS-10 nanocarbon sensor.
